<task id="010" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-10 Build `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` (Pillar 2)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>007, 008, 009</dependencies>
    <blocks>011</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, chat</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>New BFF service with critical adapter responsibility; ZERO Microsoft Agent Framework references binding (NFR-04); downstream blocker for tool-list wiring; tags `bff-api`+`ai`+`chat`.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Different file from 011; both consume this task's adapter — sequential dependency.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` — wraps an `IToolHandler` instance as a
    `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.AIFunction` so the chat-agent's LLM call sees a standard
    function-calling tool. The adapter reads `JsonSchema` from `AnalysisTool` (task 008)
    for parameter declaration, reads `AvailableInContexts` (task 007) for filtering, and
    builds the appropriate `ChatInvocationContext` (task 009) when the LLM invokes the
    tool.

    Critical-path context: this adapter is the structural bridge that lets the chat agent's
    tool list become data-driven. Tasks 011 (factory wiring) + 012 (10-tool batch migration)
    both depend on this adapter existing.

    Critical NFR-04 constraint: this task uses Microsoft.Extensions.AI ONLY (already in
    production for the existing chat-agent path). It MUST NOT introduce any Microsoft
    Agent Framework dependency or reference. The naming is `AIFunction` — the
    Microsoft.Extensions.AI primitive — NOT the Agent Framework's `AgentFunction` or any
    related type. Reviewer MUST verify zero `Microsoft.Agents.*` namespace references
    introduced by this task.

    ADR-015 binding: when the LLM invokes the wrapped function, the adapter MUST NOT log
    the user message content. Telemetry includes: tool name + decision + timestamp ONLY.
    Deterministic IDs (matterId, tenantId, sessionId) are acceptable.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with Microsoft.Extensions.AI function-calling experience. Familiar
    with the `IToolHandler` interface, `AnalysisTool` DTO, and ADR-015 trace-event hygiene.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` exists in `Services/Ai/Chat/`. Given an
    `AnalysisTool` row + corresponding `IToolHandler` impl, it produces a
    `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.AIFunction` the LLM can call. Adapter unit-tested for: valid
    JSON Schema → valid AIFunction parameter declaration; invocation passes
    `ChatInvocationContext`; telemetry emits tool name + decision + timestamp only.
    Build green; publish-size delta reported.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="interface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IToolHandler.cs</file>
    <file purpose="dto">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Models/AnalysisTool.cs</file>
    <file purpose="chat-factory">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
    <file purpose="bff-claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Register adapter inside existing `AnalysisServicesModule` per DI minimalism. ZERO new top-level Program.cs lines.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Adapter is AI-internal; CRUD-side consumers never inject it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Adapter MUST NOT log user message content. Telemetry includes tool name + decision + timestamp only. Deterministic IDs acceptable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016">Adapter respects `ai-context` rate-limit policy when adapter executes within chat-agent flow.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Verify BFF publish-size delta; ≤+5 MB R6 budget per NFR-02.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-04">ZERO Microsoft Agent Framework references in this task's code. Use Microsoft.Extensions.AI primitives only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-10">Adapter reads `JsonSchema` from `AnalysisTool` for parameter declaration; LLM sees a standard function-calling tool.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff-api/ai-function-adapter</topic>
    <files>
