  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — new chat-agent adapter + NFR-04 binding + ADR-015 trace hygiene".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 007 ✅ + 008 ✅ + 009 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Capture baseline publish size. Inspect Microsoft.Extensions.AI types currently consumed by the chat-agent path to use the same primitives consistently.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design the Adapter">
      Constructor accepts `AnalysisTool` row + `IToolHandler` instance. Builds `AIFunction` with: name from `AnalysisTool.Name`, description from `AnalysisTool.Description`, parameter schema from `AnalysisTool.JsonSchema`. Invocation: deserializes LLM args per JsonSchema; builds `ChatInvocationContext`; calls `IToolHandler.ExecuteAsync(context, args)`.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Telemetry per ADR-015">
      Emit telemetry events: `tool_call_started(toolName, decisionId, timestamp)`, `tool_call_completed(toolName, outcome, durationMs, timestamp)`. NEVER log user message content / arguments containing user message text. Deterministic IDs (tenantId, sessionId, matterId) acceptable.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Register in DI Module">
      Register inside `AnalysisServicesModule` (or appropriate existing chat module). Confirm no new Program.cs lines.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Zero Microsoft Agent Framework References">
      `grep -r "Microsoft.Agents" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` → MUST return 0 results in the adapter code path. Document in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Add Unit Tests">
      Tests: valid JSON Schema → valid AIFunction parameters; invocation builds correct `ChatInvocationContext`; telemetry events emitted with safe fields only (no user message content); invalid JSON Schema raises at construction; rate-limit policy verified if applicable.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build + Verify Publish Size">
      `dotnet build` → 0 errors. `dotnet publish -c Release` → measure delta vs baseline; report ≤+5 MB R6 budget.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk each criterion; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Verify ADR-010 / ADR-013 / ADR-015 / ADR-016 / ADR-029 + NFR-04 + FR-10 compliance. Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 010 ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report. NFR-04 verification recorded.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build, test, publish</tool>
    <tool name="git">stage + commit changes</tool>
    <tool name="code-review">Quality gate Step 9.5</tool>
    <tool name="adr-check">ADR compliance gate Step 9.5</tool>
  </tools>

