  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` exists and exposes a way to produce `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.AIFunction` from `(AnalysisTool, IToolHandler)`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">JSON Schema from `AnalysisTool.JsonSchema` becomes the AIFunction parameter declaration (FR-10).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Invocation builds correct `ChatInvocationContext` and dispatches to `IToolHandler.ExecuteAsync`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ZERO `Microsoft.Agents.*` references in the adapter code (NFR-04; grep evidence recorded).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Telemetry emits tool name + decision + timestamp only; no user message content (ADR-015).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Registered inside existing `AnalysisServicesModule` per ADR-010; no new Program.cs lines.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Adapter is AI-internal; not surfaced through PublicContracts facade (ADR-013).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta reported; ≤+5 MB R6 budget.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
